\subsection*{What is the difference between a cache hit and a cache miss?}
During an access to a memory location, a cache hit occurs if that location is mapped into cache; otherwise, a cache miss occurs.

\subsection*{Name and describe at least four cache swapping schemes.}

\begin{itemize}
\item Optimal -- the mapping which will least soon be used is replaced on cache miss.
\item LRU -- the least recently used mapping is replaced on cache miss.
\item FIFO -- the least recently added mapping is replaced on cache miss.
\item NRU -- a mapping not used within some time limit is replaced on cache miss.
\end{itemize}

