\subsection*{Name and describe the most common OS intertask communication and synchronization mechanisms.}

\begin{itemize}
\item Memory Sharing -- processes communicate by reading from and writing to shared memory.
\item Message Passing -- processes communicate by sending messages to each other's message queues.
\item Signaling -- processes communicate by raising signals or interrupts in each other's execution contexts.
\end{itemize}

\subsection*{What is segmentation?}
Segmentation is an addressing scheme which divides an address space into sets of addresses called {\it segments} which share accessibility information.

\subsection*{What are segment addresses made up of?}
Segment addresses are composed of a segment base and a segment offset.

\subsection*{What type of information can be found in a segment?}
Protection and accessibility information.

